        "timestamp": "2019-09-09 20:02:35.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nAs this is merged, I tried to trigger the portal-sdk-maven-stage-release job using key word \"stage-release\" on latest merged commit on \"portal/sdk\" repo. However, the job failed, but I do not see any error in the job console. \n\nCan you please shed some light, if you have seen this kind of behaviour before? Thanks.\n\nhttps://jenkins.onap.org/view/portal/job/portal-sdk-maven-stage-release-2.6.0/1/",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "22c9c1aea9d6de0e9e75204f937a9dc101a9a8d3",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 481,
          "name": "Jessica Wagantall",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jwagantall@linuxfoundation.org",
          "username": "jwagantall"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-09-09 20:37:26.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nYes, so this maven-stage process enforces the maven workflow more strictly. \nThis means that you will need to reflect your development towards a snapshot artifact instead of a release version. This job will take your snapshot development and produce a release. \nBasically, your pom has a version:\n<version>2.6.0</version>\nBut, you need to make sure this is a SNAPSHOT version to be able to produce a release from.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "31272795cfb04f1d5516783fbd352dd3912dcf3f",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 481,
          "name": "Jessica Wagantall",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jwagantall@linuxfoundation.org",
          "username": "jwagantall"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-09-09 20:39:01.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThere is not information in the wiki too:\nhttps://wiki.onap.org/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=68540543",
        "patchset_number": 2
      }
